1
00:00:30,427 --> 00:00:34,056
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

2
00:00:44,149 --> 00:00:46,984
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION
SOME SCENES WERE GENERATED USING AI

3
00:00:46,985 --> 00:00:49,153
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

4
00:01:04,211 --> 00:01:06,462
Woo-hoo!

5
00:01:06,463 --> 00:01:08,215
Let's go!

6
00:01:09,966 --> 00:01:12,635
My, this is nice.

7
00:01:36,159 --> 00:01:39,496
We beseech thee, mighty sea-spirit!

8
00:01:40,664 --> 00:01:43,792
"We offer this ritual today

9
00:01:44,668 --> 00:01:48,505
with all our devotion,

10
00:01:49,506 --> 00:01:53,385
praying for safety and a bountiful catch!"

11
00:01:54,177 --> 00:02:00,183
"We ask that you tame
the crashing waves and high winds,

12
00:02:01,268 --> 00:02:07,022
and fill our nets to the brim
with many schools of fish!"

13
00:02:07,023 --> 00:02:09,108
Is this your first time
seeing a sea ritual?

14
00:02:09,109 --> 00:02:10,192
Oh, yes.

15
00:02:10,193 --> 00:02:13,822
I haven't been to one
since I was little either.

16
00:02:14,531 --> 00:02:16,115
It's just the way I remember it.

17
00:02:16,116 --> 00:02:20,453
"May you also bestow your grace
upon us so that those who go out to sea

18
00:02:20,454 --> 00:02:22,205
may all return to land safely!"

19
00:02:22,914 --> 00:02:25,124
Please grant our wishes.

20
00:02:25,125 --> 00:02:28,461
Please accept our humble offering!

21
00:02:46,563 --> 00:02:48,815
- Was that a good thing?
- It's for good luck.

22
00:02:59,409 --> 00:03:00,911
What's he doing now?

23
00:03:01,828 --> 00:03:05,582
Every time they hold a sea ritual,
they store white rice in that pot.

24
00:03:06,708 --> 00:03:09,084
It's a fortune-telling practice
for the coming year.

25
00:03:09,085 --> 00:03:11,962
They say that if the rice
remains white without rotting,

26
00:03:11,963 --> 00:03:14,758
that year will bring a bountiful catch
and safety for everyone.

27
00:03:15,342 --> 00:03:16,343
Mmm.

28
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:25,060
:cue

29
00:03:37,197 --> 00:03:39,699
So… how does it look? Huh?

30
00:03:43,453 --> 00:03:45,914
Oh, come on. How is it?

31
00:03:51,670 --> 00:03:55,798
A bountiful year it is!

32
00:03:57,801 --> 00:03:59,468
All right!

33
00:03:59,469 --> 00:04:02,596
- That's great.
- Yes, that's great.

34
00:04:02,597 --> 00:04:04,431
Bless you all!

35
00:04:04,432 --> 00:04:06,392
- Bless you!
- Give me a lot.

36
00:04:06,393 --> 00:04:08,894
Give me a lot.

37
00:04:08,895 --> 00:04:09,979
A lot.

38
00:04:09,980 --> 00:04:12,189
Here's to a bountiful year of fish.

39
00:04:12,190 --> 00:04:15,276
Jangsu, we're in for a year of plenty!

40
00:04:15,277 --> 00:04:19,155
Gosh!

41
00:04:20,824 --> 00:04:23,158
Here, bless you all.

42
00:04:23,159 --> 00:04:25,412
Bless you!

43
00:04:39,926 --> 00:04:42,095
- Oh, no!
- Oh, no!

44
00:04:43,138 --> 00:04:44,513
Oh, no!

45
00:04:45,724 --> 00:04:47,516
Wait. Please don't touch it.

46
00:04:49,728 --> 00:04:51,229
- Oh, my!
-  Let me see.

47
00:04:51,980 --> 00:04:54,858
The rice, the pot… How could this happen?

48
00:04:56,401 --> 00:04:58,695
Goodness!

49
00:05:00,196 --> 00:05:05,659
EPISODE 10
IT'S NOT OKAY.

50
00:05:21,885 --> 00:05:23,053
Goodness…

51
00:05:44,908 --> 00:05:47,034
I ruined the sea ritual
as the village chief.

52
00:05:47,035 --> 00:05:48,453
What am I to do now?

53
00:05:50,330 --> 00:05:52,707
It looked like just a pot to me.

54
00:05:54,793 --> 00:05:57,544
That was no mere pot.

55
00:05:57,545 --> 00:06:01,800
A year's worth of good fortune
for Pyeondongdo rested on that sacred pot.

56
00:06:02,384 --> 00:06:03,677
I see…

57
00:06:10,433 --> 00:06:14,520
Right. Weren't you moving
back into your house today, Ms. Hari?

58
00:06:14,521 --> 00:06:15,938
Yes, today's the day.

59
00:06:15,939 --> 00:06:19,567
My, I'm sure it couldn't have been easy,
what with the construction dragging on.

60
00:06:20,652 --> 00:06:22,444
And you had your work cut out for you,

61
00:06:22,445 --> 00:06:24,406
cleaning up the house every night.

62
00:06:31,621 --> 00:06:33,497
We're done. Thank you for your patience.

63
00:06:33,498 --> 00:06:36,875
-  Thank you.
- Have a safe trip back.

64
00:06:36,876 --> 00:06:38,544
- Okay.
-  Goodbye.

65
00:06:49,222 --> 00:06:50,348
Dr. Do.
:cue

66
00:06:53,351 --> 00:06:55,270
Should we throw
a housewarming party today?

67
00:06:57,355 --> 00:06:58,856
Mmm.

68
00:07:11,161 --> 00:07:13,204
Whoa.

69
00:07:14,664 --> 00:07:17,958
It's just the way I remember it.
How did you find the time to do this?

70
00:07:35,268 --> 00:07:36,269
Hmm.

71
00:07:39,189 --> 00:07:40,856
I brought you a housewarming gift.

72
00:07:40,857 --> 00:07:42,400
Hmm? What is it?

73
00:07:47,530 --> 00:07:49,199
It's fried chicken!

74
00:07:50,158 --> 00:07:53,702
I pulled some strings with Mr. Park
since we're having a party.

75
00:08:01,294 --> 00:08:02,503
- Here.
- Thank you.

76
00:08:02,504 --> 00:08:04,506
I was actually going to eat with my hands.

77
00:08:06,883 --> 00:08:07,884
It's good.

78
00:08:09,761 --> 00:08:11,887
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

79
00:08:11,888 --> 00:08:15,265
When I retire, I'm going to set up
my own fried chicken place,

80
00:08:15,266 --> 00:08:16,851
so I can eat it every day.

81
00:08:17,519 --> 00:08:18,645
Mmm.

82
00:08:19,354 --> 00:08:21,731
But are you sure
they fixed these properly to last?

83
00:08:22,774 --> 00:08:24,525
Why? Everything seems okay.

84
00:08:24,526 --> 00:08:27,487
I'm just worried
they might have done a hack job.

85
00:08:32,283 --> 00:08:36,830
I'm just a little bummed out
that you're no longer at the quarters.

86
00:08:38,164 --> 00:08:40,667
What's there to be bummed out about?
This is even better.

87
00:08:41,709 --> 00:08:42,918
What?

88
00:08:44,045 --> 00:08:48,550
Well, the other doctors
are at the quarters, so…

89
00:08:50,093 --> 00:08:52,427
What did you want to do if we were alone?

90
00:08:52,428 --> 00:08:56,181
It's not like I wanted to do anything.

91
00:08:56,182 --> 00:09:00,562
It was just inconvenient having to text
with a wall between us. That's all.

92
00:09:02,981 --> 00:09:05,108
What do you want to do
now that there's no wall?

93
00:09:06,234 --> 00:09:07,651
Stop teasing me.

94
00:09:07,652 --> 00:09:10,404
If you want to do something,
feel free to do it.

95
00:09:10,405 --> 00:09:12,907
There's no wall between us here
and we're all alone.

96
00:09:13,491 --> 00:09:16,327
Oh, come on!
That's not what I mean.

97
00:09:44,898 --> 00:09:46,273
You're getting a call.

98
00:09:46,274 --> 00:09:47,774
Oh, it-it's probably a spam call.

99
00:09:47,775 --> 00:09:49,277
- I've been getting a lot.
- Mmm.

100
00:09:58,661 --> 00:10:00,829
I think you should get that.

101
00:10:00,830 --> 00:10:02,081
Right.

102
00:10:04,042 --> 00:10:05,834
- Hello?
-  Goodness, Dr. Do!

103
00:10:05,835 --> 00:10:08,420
What took you so long to answer?

104
00:10:08,421 --> 00:10:10,798
You have to hurry over
to the center right now!

105
00:10:11,507 --> 00:10:12,926
Uh, okay.
:cue

106
00:10:20,099 --> 00:10:21,391
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

107
00:10:21,392 --> 00:10:23,353
Goodness,
it hurts so much.

108
00:10:24,103 --> 00:10:25,395
What's the matter?

109
00:10:25,396 --> 00:10:27,232
Here. Over here…

110
00:10:28,024 --> 00:10:29,775
Let me take a look.

111
00:10:31,611 --> 00:10:33,446
Goodness!

112
00:10:34,447 --> 00:10:35,989
How about here?

113
00:10:35,990 --> 00:10:37,324
So this spot is fine.

114
00:10:37,325 --> 00:10:38,617
What about here?

115
00:10:38,618 --> 00:10:40,369
No issues here either.

116
00:10:42,455 --> 00:10:44,289
Oh! Oh, man!

117
00:10:44,290 --> 00:10:46,166
Does it hurt when I press down
or when I let go?

118
00:10:46,167 --> 00:10:47,876
I don't know.

119
00:10:47,877 --> 00:10:49,503
- I'll try pressing again.
- Okay.

120
00:10:52,298 --> 00:10:55,300
Oh, goodness! Goodness!

121
00:10:55,301 --> 00:10:56,468
How long has it hurt?

122
00:10:56,469 --> 00:10:58,804
For the past few days, I think.

123
00:10:58,805 --> 00:11:02,976
The pain is killing
me, so please make it go away.

124
00:11:04,686 --> 00:11:07,688
Pain upon removal of pressure
from the lower right abdomen,

125
00:11:07,689 --> 00:11:09,398
a typical symptom of appendicitis.

126
00:11:09,399 --> 00:11:12,568
My goodness, please help me.

127
00:11:13,278 --> 00:11:15,320
You need to go
to a big hospital right now.

128
00:11:15,321 --> 00:11:17,614
I'm not sure,
but I suspect you have appendicitis.

129
00:11:17,615 --> 00:11:19,826
- What is that?
- Your appendix may have burst.

130
00:11:21,744 --> 00:11:24,122
- I'll hail us a medical boat.
- Okay.

131
00:11:25,498 --> 00:11:27,083
I'll give you a painkiller for now.

132
00:11:29,877 --> 00:11:31,254
You can relax your hand.

133
00:11:38,511 --> 00:11:41,763
The seas are too rough for a medical boat,

134
00:11:41,764 --> 00:11:44,434
but a chopper is available,
so I requested it.

135
00:11:45,518 --> 00:11:47,186
- Let's go.
- Okay.

136
00:11:53,735 --> 00:11:55,819
Hang in there, sir.
We're almost there.

137
00:12:05,413 --> 00:12:07,664
They got here earlier than expected.

138
00:12:07,665 --> 00:12:08,666
What a relief.

139
00:12:09,542 --> 00:12:12,461
We're almost there.

140
00:12:12,462 --> 00:12:16,716
Hang in there just a little longer.

141
00:12:51,709 --> 00:12:55,087
An emergency dispatch
helicopter sent to transfer a patient

142
00:12:55,088 --> 00:12:57,255
out of Pyeondongdo, Yeopoong-gun,
has crashed,

143
00:12:57,256 --> 00:13:02,135
resulting in the death of the pilot,
Mr. Kim Hongcheol, who was 34 years old.

144
00:13:02,136 --> 00:13:05,931
Fire authorities launched an investigation
and are going over the CCTV footage

145
00:13:05,932 --> 00:13:08,017
to find out the cause of the incident.

146
00:13:08,726 --> 00:13:11,812
Fire authorities believe the fatal crash
may have occurred

147
00:13:11,813 --> 00:13:15,607
while the pilot attempted a risky landing
to save an emergency patient.

148
00:13:15,608 --> 00:13:18,110
Meanwhile, the patient suspected
of having appendicitis

149
00:13:18,111 --> 00:13:21,029
turned out to have nothing more
than an upset stomach,

150
00:13:21,030 --> 00:13:22,989
adding to the tragedy.

151
00:13:22,990 --> 00:13:26,743
It is a horrific incident caused by
a public health doctor's misdiagnosis.

152
00:13:26,744 --> 00:13:29,621
In the wake of this tragedy,
concerns regarding the misdiagnoses

153
00:13:29,622 --> 00:13:32,416
of incompetent public health doctors
are growing,

154
00:13:32,417 --> 00:13:35,252
pushing Governor Ko of Yeopoong-gun,
to bow his head

155
00:13:35,253 --> 00:13:37,754
and apologize on behalf
of the Pyeondong Health Center.

156
00:13:37,755 --> 00:13:39,673
First of all,

157
00:13:39,674 --> 00:13:44,136
I'd like to express my sincerest
condolences to Mr. Kim Hongcheol,

158
00:13:44,137 --> 00:13:46,638
who lost his life
to an unfortunate accident,

159
00:13:46,639 --> 00:13:49,142
and to the family of the deceased.
:cue

160
00:13:51,769 --> 00:13:52,853
The thing is,

161
00:13:52,854 --> 00:13:58,608
our investigation into the PH docs
has revealed quite a lot of issues.

162
00:13:58,609 --> 00:14:02,028
Why are they blaming the PH docs
for a helicopter crash?

163
00:14:02,029 --> 00:14:04,990
The way they tried to transfer

164
00:14:04,991 --> 00:14:07,576
a patient without
a proper diagnosis, right?

165
00:14:07,577 --> 00:14:10,787
They were in such a hurry to move him,
you know?

166
00:14:10,788 --> 00:14:13,665
Such decisions led
to this tragic accident.

167
00:14:13,666 --> 00:14:18,044
Maybe he should provide us
with better equipment then!

168
00:14:18,045 --> 00:14:25,011
People always need someone to blame
when a major accident happens.

169
00:14:27,930 --> 00:14:30,891
Is Dr. Do doing okay?
I noticed he even took a leave of absence.

170
00:14:30,892 --> 00:14:32,517
I'm sorry.

171
00:14:32,518 --> 00:14:34,978
He hasn't come out of his room
since the accident.

172
00:14:34,979 --> 00:14:36,396
I'm so sorry.

173
00:14:36,397 --> 00:14:37,607
Just turn it off.

174
00:14:38,566 --> 00:14:41,360
Of course he's struggling.
The whole world just turned on him.

175
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:47,283
But he's not going to get through this
if he doesn't eat.

176
00:15:13,184 --> 00:15:14,602
Dr. Do, it's me.

177
00:15:16,354 --> 00:15:17,980
You should at least eat.

178
00:15:24,111 --> 00:15:26,363
Dr. Do, it was just an accident.

179
00:15:26,364 --> 00:15:27,949
It wasn't your fault.

180
00:15:41,796 --> 00:15:42,797
But still…

181
00:15:45,258 --> 00:15:48,344
If the pain gets unbearable,
come and lean on me.

182
00:15:52,431 --> 00:15:55,267
I promised I'd stay
by your side, remember?

183
00:15:57,061 --> 00:15:58,062
Okay?

184
00:16:41,689 --> 00:16:44,566
Oh, my. Oh, my.
You have to try this right now.

185
00:16:44,567 --> 00:16:45,650
"Ah, ah." Say "ah."

186
00:16:46,736 --> 00:16:49,654
- I'm a little queasy.
- Why are you feeling queasy?

187
00:16:49,655 --> 00:16:54,451
I think it's PMS.
I feel so bloated every time.

188
00:16:54,452 --> 00:16:57,329
If it's giving you a hard time,
take some meds.

189
00:16:57,330 --> 00:16:59,456
It won't get better
if you try to endure it.

190
00:16:59,457 --> 00:17:00,832
Okay.

191
00:17:00,833 --> 00:17:03,793
Why is everyone starving themselves, huh?

192
00:17:03,794 --> 00:17:05,837
Eating some food makes everything better.

193
00:17:05,838 --> 00:17:10,550
Dealing with sadness on an empty stomach
makes things worse.

194
00:17:10,551 --> 00:17:12,427
I made this with local ingredients…

195
00:17:12,428 --> 00:17:14,971
YOUR PERIOD IS 13 DAYS OVERDUE

196
00:17:14,972 --> 00:17:17,683
-  Thirteen days overdue…
-  Why won't you have any?

197
00:17:19,185 --> 00:17:22,188
An empty stomach
leads to sadness and illness.

198
00:17:23,606 --> 00:17:25,441
Can't believe you're not having this.
:cue

199
00:17:28,194 --> 00:17:30,987
- Granny, I'm here.
-  Oh, my.

200
00:17:30,988 --> 00:17:33,490
Uh, what are you doing here
at this time? Huh?

201
00:17:33,491 --> 00:17:36,618
Oh, we ran out of toilet paper
at the center.

202
00:17:36,619 --> 00:17:38,119
Oh, really?

203
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:40,539
Uh, how's Dr. Do doing?

204
00:17:42,333 --> 00:17:45,210
He seems to think it's all his fault.

205
00:17:45,211 --> 00:17:46,878
He won't even come out of his room.

206
00:17:46,879 --> 00:17:48,922
Goodness gracious me.

207
00:17:48,923 --> 00:17:51,591
The whole world's
talking about him like that after all.

208
00:17:51,592 --> 00:17:52,885
I feel so bad for him.

209
00:17:53,886 --> 00:17:56,596
Even if he's shut his doors
and won't come outside,

210
00:17:56,597 --> 00:17:58,556
you should linger outside his room often.

211
00:17:58,557 --> 00:18:02,977
You have to keep pestering him so he knows
that he's got someone on his side.

212
00:18:02,978 --> 00:18:04,354
It's the same with islands.

213
00:18:04,355 --> 00:18:07,399
An island by itself is just
a deserted island where no one can live.

214
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:10,610
The islands need people
to keep hopping between them

215
00:18:10,611 --> 00:18:12,779
and stay connected for them
to become habitable, eh.

216
00:18:12,780 --> 00:18:14,323
Mmm.

217
00:18:20,496 --> 00:18:21,871
Hmm?

218
00:18:21,872 --> 00:18:23,248
Oh, why are you crying?

219
00:18:23,249 --> 00:18:25,125
- Grandma.
- Why are you crying?

220
00:18:25,126 --> 00:18:26,960
Oh, gosh, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

221
00:18:26,961 --> 00:18:29,296
She tripped because of me,
and her doll got a little…

222
00:18:31,590 --> 00:18:33,049
Don't cry.

223
00:18:33,050 --> 00:18:35,301
I'll get you another one, okay?

224
00:18:35,302 --> 00:18:39,724
I don't want another doll!

225
00:18:40,307 --> 00:18:43,059
There's only one Tosun!

226
00:18:43,060 --> 00:18:45,270
Then we just need to stitch her up.

227
00:18:45,271 --> 00:18:48,773
Don't cry, okay? Stop crying.

228
00:18:48,774 --> 00:18:51,068
Stop crying now.

229
00:18:53,028 --> 00:18:57,283
If you're okay with it,
can I help you treat Tosun?

230
00:18:57,867 --> 00:18:59,367
- Mmm.
-  Hmm?

231
00:18:59,368 --> 00:19:00,953
I'm pretty sure I can do it.

232
00:19:45,414 --> 00:19:46,415
Wow.

233
00:20:10,272 --> 00:20:13,609
There, all done. Here.

234
00:20:14,527 --> 00:20:17,905
Wow, she's as good as new.

235
00:20:18,614 --> 00:20:20,741
Then you're going to
forgive me now, right?

236
00:20:21,784 --> 00:20:23,911
Thanks.

237
00:20:34,713 --> 00:20:38,259
LUCKY SUPERMARKET

238
00:20:46,141 --> 00:20:47,476
Where could it be?

239
00:20:48,853 --> 00:20:50,353
Are you a surgeon?

240
00:20:50,354 --> 00:20:52,398
How could you tell?

241
00:20:52,898 --> 00:20:54,983
I used to be an OR nurse.

242
00:20:54,984 --> 00:20:56,276
Ah!

243
00:20:56,277 --> 00:20:57,652
No wonder we clicked so well.

244
00:20:59,154 --> 00:21:00,155
Wait.

245
00:21:00,656 --> 00:21:03,826
Then are you a nurse
at the Pyeondong Health Center?

246
00:21:04,618 --> 00:21:06,619
- I am.
-  That's great.

247
00:21:06,620 --> 00:21:08,997
- Maybe you can help me.
- Mmm.

248
00:21:08,998 --> 00:21:12,501
I'm here to meet Jiui
at the Pyeondong Health Center.
:cue

249
00:21:13,419 --> 00:21:14,752
Dr. Do Jiui?

250
00:21:14,753 --> 00:21:16,380
Mmm.

251
00:21:31,312 --> 00:21:32,313
Who's that?

252
00:21:32,938 --> 00:21:35,107
She said she's a friend of Dr. Do Jiui.

253
00:21:36,317 --> 00:21:38,444
-  A friend.
- A friend.

254
00:21:40,487 --> 00:21:41,488
A friend?

255
00:21:42,239 --> 00:21:45,575
But do you think he'll come down for her?

256
00:21:45,576 --> 00:21:48,411
He hasn't opened his door for days.

257
00:21:53,167 --> 00:21:55,668
Oh. There he is.

258
00:22:03,177 --> 00:22:06,263
Come outside with me.

259
00:22:33,916 --> 00:22:34,917
Why are you here?

260
00:22:38,712 --> 00:22:40,130
You look terrible.

261
00:22:44,802 --> 00:22:48,889
I came running as soon as I saw the news.
I knew you would be like this.

262
00:22:52,267 --> 00:22:55,561
Appendicitis is often tricky to diagnose.

263
00:22:55,562 --> 00:22:57,647
The media has no idea
what they're talking about

264
00:22:57,648 --> 00:22:59,400
pinning the blame on you.

265
00:23:02,361 --> 00:23:03,904
Please just leave.

266
00:23:05,698 --> 00:23:08,575
- Jiui--
- Why couldn't you console me back then?

267
00:23:11,787 --> 00:23:13,330
After Seonu's death…

268
00:23:15,749 --> 00:23:18,168
that's what I wanted
to hear from you most.

269
00:23:21,755 --> 00:23:25,174
They don't seem to be on good terms,
so I wonder why she's here.

270
00:23:25,175 --> 00:23:26,677
Especially at a time like this.

271
00:23:34,435 --> 00:23:37,271
SUGWANG BAIT AND TACKLE SHOP

272
00:23:47,781 --> 00:23:49,742
It's an emergency! Emergency!

273
00:23:53,162 --> 00:23:55,122
- Let me check your temperature first.
- Okay.

274
00:23:55,789 --> 00:23:58,583
Sir, you're just feeling
a little queasy, right?

275
00:23:58,584 --> 00:24:00,626
Send the urgent patients to me first.

276
00:24:00,627 --> 00:24:01,961
- Okay.
- Do you feel any pain,

277
00:24:01,962 --> 00:24:03,588
or do you just feel nauseated?

278
00:24:03,589 --> 00:24:06,007
- Let me take you to the exam room.
- I feel nauseated.

279
00:24:06,008 --> 00:24:07,967
Goodness, I feel like I'm dying.

280
00:24:07,968 --> 00:24:11,220
- What seems to be the problem?
- My insides are acting up like crazy.

281
00:24:11,221 --> 00:24:13,931
Huh? Whoa. I think we need
to check this patient first.

282
00:24:13,932 --> 00:24:15,600
- Use this to clean it up.
- Okay.

283
00:24:15,601 --> 00:24:18,312
I'll take a look at him in my room.
Are you okay, sir?

284
00:24:19,688 --> 00:24:21,482
- Come with me, sir.
- Okay.

285
00:24:22,316 --> 00:24:24,609
Goodness, this is killing me.

286
00:24:24,610 --> 00:24:25,736
- This way?
-  Yes.

287
00:24:26,445 --> 00:24:27,528
What happened?

288
00:24:27,529 --> 00:24:30,490
They came here on a group tour,
and they all shared some gimbap.

289
00:24:30,491 --> 00:24:33,076
- Where is your discomfort?
- Right, well…

290
00:24:36,747 --> 00:24:39,291
You're the doctor who was on TV.

291
00:24:40,375 --> 00:24:44,129
I was kind of hoping to get examined
by a different doctor.

292
00:24:45,714 --> 00:24:47,924
Uh, I've, uh, got an underlying condition,

293
00:24:47,925 --> 00:24:50,802
so I'm just worried
that something terrible might happen

294
00:24:50,803 --> 00:24:52,804
if I were to take the wrong meds.

295
00:24:52,805 --> 00:24:56,599
- Sir, this doctor here is also--
- I-It's okay. It's okay. It's okay.

296
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:58,184
I'm an ER doctor.
:cue

297
00:24:58,185 --> 00:25:00,604
If it's all right with you,
may I take a look?

298
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:04,441
Okay.

299
00:25:05,317 --> 00:25:06,985
Sir, I'm going to take your pulse.

300
00:25:08,112 --> 00:25:10,446
You're urinating less
or it's gotten darker, right?

301
00:25:10,447 --> 00:25:13,116
Gosh…  …everything I drink
just passes right through me.

302
00:25:13,117 --> 00:25:15,952
He's going to be dehydrated.
Prep an IV please.

303
00:25:15,953 --> 00:25:18,037
- Okay.
- Let's get you on an IV first.

304
00:25:18,038 --> 00:25:19,622
Okay.

305
00:25:19,623 --> 00:25:23,377
Goodness gracious me, this is torture.

306
00:25:36,890 --> 00:25:40,101
I'm Lee Hwayeong,
an ER doctor from Samjeong Hospital.

307
00:25:40,102 --> 00:25:42,312
I'd like to offer my assistance
if you don't mind.

308
00:25:44,773 --> 00:25:47,650
We should sort the patients
by their symptoms first.

309
00:25:47,651 --> 00:25:50,069
Even if they got ill from the same food,

310
00:25:50,070 --> 00:25:51,988
we can't give them the same prescription.

311
00:25:55,450 --> 00:25:57,285
We'll be sorting the patients now.

312
00:25:57,286 --> 00:26:00,705
People with uneasy stomachs,
people experiencing dehydration,

313
00:26:00,706 --> 00:26:02,457
and those with stomach pain.

314
00:26:04,543 --> 00:26:06,627
It hurts a bit there.

315
00:26:06,628 --> 00:26:08,839
- But it's not a sharp pain, is it?
- No.

316
00:26:10,299 --> 00:26:12,801
You said you had diarrhea.
Are you also running a fever?

317
00:26:13,802 --> 00:26:15,761
Let me take a look at you, sir.

318
00:26:15,762 --> 00:26:17,806
Could you lift up your shirt a little?

319
00:26:20,350 --> 00:26:22,519
Please clench your fist for me.

320
00:26:25,063 --> 00:26:27,315
Anyone here experiencing abdominal pain?

321
00:26:27,316 --> 00:26:28,900
Anyone having diarrhea?

322
00:26:28,901 --> 00:26:31,737
-  How does this feel?
- Do you have abdominal pain?

323
00:26:37,075 --> 00:26:40,578
The nausea will go away soon,
but the diarrhea will last a few days.

324
00:26:40,579 --> 00:26:43,749
- I'll prescribe you medicine for both.
- Okay.

325
00:26:48,128 --> 00:26:50,964
Three times a day for five days.
Make sure you take all of them.

326
00:26:54,509 --> 00:26:56,093
Your abdominal pain's mostly gone?

327
00:26:56,094 --> 00:26:57,178
- Yes.
- Right.

328
00:26:57,179 --> 00:26:59,473
So you're feeling nauseous,
and you have a migraine.

329
00:27:01,767 --> 00:27:03,476
This should be fine.

330
00:27:03,477 --> 00:27:07,064
But if your symptoms get worse,
be sure to visit a hospital.

331
00:27:22,245 --> 00:27:24,539
- Drink lots of water, okay?
- Thank you.

332
00:27:28,418 --> 00:27:30,212
Wow.

333
00:27:33,966 --> 00:27:39,428
Oh, gosh, things could have really turned
ugly had it not been for you, doctor.

334
00:27:39,429 --> 00:27:43,516
When those patients started flooding in,
I was in full-blown panic mode.

335
00:27:43,517 --> 00:27:45,059
I don't know how to thank you.

336
00:27:45,060 --> 00:27:47,562
Please don't mention it.
I'm just glad I could help.

337
00:27:49,690 --> 00:27:51,233
I'm going to go upstairs now.

338
00:27:55,153 --> 00:27:56,488
Can I get something to eat?

339
00:27:58,073 --> 00:27:59,908
I haven't had anything to eat all day.

340
00:28:02,369 --> 00:28:04,579
Let's eat. I'm starving.

341
00:28:13,964 --> 00:28:16,008
I'm going to my room now.
Good work, everyone.

342
00:28:27,352 --> 00:28:28,978
- Let's eat.
- Let's eat.

343
00:28:28,979 --> 00:28:30,229
- Let's eat.
- Mmm.

344
00:28:30,230 --> 00:28:32,773
Sounds good. Le-Let's eat.
Let's eat.

345
00:28:32,774 --> 00:28:34,316
You haven't eaten all day.

346
00:28:34,317 --> 00:28:37,486
Let's go outside.
Let's go eat at Cliffside.

347
00:28:37,487 --> 00:28:38,571
Cliffside?

348
00:28:38,572 --> 00:28:39,865
S-Sounds good.
:cue

349
00:28:48,331 --> 00:28:49,415
Mmm!

350
00:28:49,416 --> 00:28:52,251
The food here is delicious. Wow!

351
00:28:52,252 --> 00:28:53,919
I'm glad you like it.

352
00:28:53,920 --> 00:28:56,380
I was worried
it might not be to your liking,

353
00:28:56,381 --> 00:28:59,717
since you're from the city and all.

354
00:28:59,718 --> 00:29:04,139
By the way, how do you know Dr. Do…

355
00:29:05,390 --> 00:29:07,850
Oh, I was just curious.

356
00:29:07,851 --> 00:29:09,977
Since you came all this way,
you seem close,

357
00:29:09,978 --> 00:29:13,856
but at the same time…
…you don't seem that close.

358
00:29:14,941 --> 00:29:17,069
-  Stop it.
- Jiui and I…

359
00:29:19,780 --> 00:29:22,156
used to date in university
for about five years.

360
00:29:22,157 --> 00:29:24,743
- Huh?
-  Five years?

361
00:29:25,243 --> 00:29:28,412
Oh, five years go by in a flash.
It's nothing, really.

362
00:29:28,413 --> 00:29:30,915
I've never even dated someone
for five whole years.

363
00:29:30,916 --> 00:29:33,125
Would you just…
She's right here.

364
00:29:33,126 --> 00:29:35,086
Uh, oh, oh.

365
00:29:35,087 --> 00:29:38,631
So you only dated for five years, huh?

366
00:29:38,632 --> 00:29:39,965
I see.

367
00:29:39,966 --> 00:29:42,301
That's when you're still young and naive.

368
00:29:42,302 --> 00:29:44,930
Yeah, college kids are practically babies.

369
00:29:46,431 --> 00:29:50,227
I felt like I had to come here
when I saw Jiui on the news.

370
00:29:51,103 --> 00:29:52,896
I know Jiui better than anyone else.

371
00:29:54,272 --> 00:29:56,732
-  Let's see now.
-  Au-Auntie, what is that?

372
00:29:56,733 --> 00:30:00,277
Oh, I was going to ask you
to get these to Dr. Do Jiui.

373
00:30:00,278 --> 00:30:03,823
You know what they say about how
an aching heart feeds off hunger.

374
00:30:03,824 --> 00:30:06,200
In times like this,
we should just keep feeding him.

375
00:30:06,201 --> 00:30:07,785
-  Give it to me.
- Uh-huh.

376
00:30:07,786 --> 00:30:09,246
I'll get it to--

377
00:30:10,622 --> 00:30:12,165
You should give it to him, Ms. Yuk.

378
00:30:12,958 --> 00:30:14,041
What?

379
00:30:14,042 --> 00:30:17,879
You're the one
Dr. Do needs most right now.

380
00:30:19,297 --> 00:30:20,756
Right.

381
00:30:20,757 --> 00:30:23,634
Oh, you're right.
Ms. Hari should go.

382
00:30:23,635 --> 00:30:27,012
It's not like we'd be of any use to him
in this situation, right?

383
00:30:27,013 --> 00:30:30,516
- You should hurry or it'll get cold.
-  Go make sure he eats it.

384
00:30:30,517 --> 00:30:32,810
- I-I'll be going then.
-  Right.

385
00:30:32,811 --> 00:30:34,645
Get it to him before it gets cold, okay?

386
00:30:34,646 --> 00:30:36,731
- Thanks, Auntie.
- Here you go.

387
00:30:40,652 --> 00:30:42,319
Thank you for your help today.

388
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:44,239
Yes, of course. Mmm.

389
00:30:45,198 --> 00:30:47,159
Mmm. There she goes.

390
00:30:57,836 --> 00:30:59,045
Ms. Yuk.

391
00:30:59,713 --> 00:31:01,006
Huh?

392
00:31:05,552 --> 00:31:09,847
If you really are
the person Jiui needs most right now,

393
00:31:09,848 --> 00:31:13,685
please convince him to leave this island.

394
00:31:14,394 --> 00:31:15,477
What?

395
00:31:15,478 --> 00:31:17,646
I've looked into it,

396
00:31:17,647 --> 00:31:20,608
and there's a way for PH docs
to be transferred.

397
00:31:20,609 --> 00:31:23,403
- Jiui can get out of this--
- What do you mean by that?

398
00:31:24,321 --> 00:31:27,324
Why should he have to leave?
He did nothing wrong.

399
00:31:28,116 --> 00:31:30,243
I didn't mean that he did something wrong.

400
00:31:31,578 --> 00:31:33,913
I'm sure you've seen it for yourself.

401
00:31:33,914 --> 00:31:35,165
Jiui's really struggling.

402
00:31:36,917 --> 00:31:41,253
Living here must have been hell for Jiui.

403
00:31:41,254 --> 00:31:44,549
It must have reminded him of Seonu,
and he must have blamed himself.

404
00:31:46,092 --> 00:31:47,510
Seonu?

405
00:31:49,888 --> 00:31:50,889
Oh.

406
00:31:52,182 --> 00:31:56,728
Then I guess you have no idea
why an island would be hell for Jiui.

407
00:32:02,275 --> 00:32:03,902
- Jiui--
- I think…

408
00:32:06,238 --> 00:32:08,907
I'd rather hear it directly from him.

409
00:32:11,660 --> 00:32:13,161
I'll be going now.

410
00:32:50,532 --> 00:32:55,161
Then I guess you have no idea
why an island would be hell for Jiui.
:cue

411
00:33:20,353 --> 00:33:24,190
I guess Ms. Hari had to
just leave it here.

412
00:33:27,235 --> 00:33:28,736
I get it, though.

413
00:33:28,737 --> 00:33:31,238
I have no idea
how we should console him either,

414
00:33:31,239 --> 00:33:34,034
since he's shut the door on us like this.

415
00:33:38,955 --> 00:33:39,956
Dr. Do Jiui.

416
00:33:42,250 --> 00:33:43,251
Dr. Do Jiui!

417
00:33:53,845 --> 00:33:55,013
What is it?

418
00:33:55,597 --> 00:33:56,765
You should eat.

419
00:34:01,770 --> 00:34:03,396
I'll eat later.

420
00:34:06,775 --> 00:34:08,109
Eat right now.

421
00:34:08,777 --> 00:34:10,487
Everyone's worried about you.

422
00:34:16,743 --> 00:34:19,661
DON'T SKIP YOUR MEALS, DR. DO

423
00:34:36,513 --> 00:34:38,472
Hurry up and dig in.

424
00:34:38,473 --> 00:34:40,016
It's seasoned perfectly today.

425
00:34:44,270 --> 00:34:47,399
I'm sorry to put you all through this.

426
00:34:49,943 --> 00:34:53,071
Please don't beat yourself up
too much over it, Dr. Do.

427
00:34:54,364 --> 00:34:57,450
You were only trying to save a patient.

428
00:35:03,248 --> 00:35:06,334
Anyone would have made the same call.

429
00:35:14,134 --> 00:35:15,135
Do you really…

430
00:35:18,555 --> 00:35:19,556
think so?

431
00:35:26,438 --> 00:35:27,439
These days…

432
00:35:30,150 --> 00:35:31,776
I'm so scared of being a doctor.

433
00:35:35,822 --> 00:35:37,323
I'm so clueless about everything…

434
00:35:39,159 --> 00:35:40,660
and I still have so much to learn,

435
00:35:43,246 --> 00:35:44,664
so the fact that so many lives…

436
00:35:46,875 --> 00:35:49,085
depend on the decisions I make…

437
00:35:54,215 --> 00:35:55,216
really scares me.

438
00:36:00,889 --> 00:36:05,477
Did you both dream of becoming doctors
right from the start?

439
00:36:11,649 --> 00:36:16,070
To be honest, I only became a doctor
because everyone said I should.

440
00:36:17,071 --> 00:36:20,658
Because they said studying hard
and becoming a doctor was the dream.

441
00:36:22,035 --> 00:36:27,207
So I studied like my life depended on it,
and one day, before I knew it…

442
00:36:29,375 --> 00:36:31,628
people called me "doctor."

443
00:36:33,505 --> 00:36:35,799
I suddenly had to start treating patients.

444
00:36:37,175 --> 00:36:43,973
Man, I was so nervous my hands
were shaking like crazy, you know?

445
00:36:48,311 --> 00:36:49,521
I'm sure it's…

446
00:36:51,773 --> 00:36:53,942
the same for everyone here.

447
00:36:57,445 --> 00:36:58,696
You too, Dr. Hyeon?

448
00:37:00,156 --> 00:37:02,366
It didn't seem like it.

449
00:37:02,367 --> 00:37:04,118
I get scared every time.

450
00:37:05,495 --> 00:37:09,123
Sometimes, I just want to hide.

451
00:37:31,688 --> 00:37:33,022
:cue

452
00:37:35,483 --> 00:37:36,567
WINTER FLU VACCINATION

453
00:37:36,568 --> 00:37:39,528
- Can I have your name?
- It's Kim Malsun.

454
00:37:39,529 --> 00:37:43,532
Ms. Kim Malsun,
are you feeling unwell today?

455
00:37:43,533 --> 00:37:44,783
Not really.

456
00:37:44,784 --> 00:37:45,868
I see.

457
00:37:45,869 --> 00:37:47,953
- Let me check your temperature for you.
- Okay.

458
00:37:47,954 --> 00:37:50,874
PYEONDONGDO FLU VACCINATION

459
00:37:52,125 --> 00:37:55,752
-  Are you allergic to anything?
-  Oh, no.

460
00:37:55,753 --> 00:37:57,588
Have you ever experienced side effects…

461
00:37:57,589 --> 00:37:59,131
You're a real trooper.

462
00:37:59,132 --> 00:38:00,215
My, that does sting.

463
00:38:00,216 --> 00:38:02,677
Don't rub it.
Just keep applying pressure, please.

464
00:38:05,430 --> 00:38:11,268
Goodness, you're all working so hard.
Have some of this while you work.

465
00:38:11,269 --> 00:38:12,687
- Thank you, Mr. Park.
- Thank you.

466
00:38:14,105 --> 00:38:16,565
We've had an amazing turnout
from the residents today.

467
00:38:16,566 --> 00:38:19,694
It must be because you did
such a great job promoting this.

468
00:38:21,029 --> 00:38:25,657
Well, actually, it's not because
I promoted it well or anything.

469
00:38:25,658 --> 00:38:27,409
They're just scared they might die.

470
00:38:27,410 --> 00:38:29,245
- What?
- Everyone's…

471
00:38:31,122 --> 00:38:32,539
Anxious.

472
00:38:32,540 --> 00:38:36,376
That falling ill on an island
could really mean certain death.

473
00:38:36,377 --> 00:38:38,211
A helicopter crashed here,

474
00:38:38,212 --> 00:38:41,798
and over yonder on Jangmokdo,
a granny passed away

475
00:38:41,799 --> 00:38:45,010
from a heart attack
because she couldn't get to a hospital.

476
00:38:45,011 --> 00:38:48,096
But they have a health center
and a helipad there.

477
00:38:48,097 --> 00:38:49,765
Some good that helipad did.

478
00:38:49,766 --> 00:38:52,059
The chopper couldn't even land
and had to leave.

479
00:38:52,060 --> 00:38:55,062
They didn't even put
the finishing touches on those helipads

480
00:38:55,063 --> 00:38:57,606
despite all that crap
they pulled to get them made.

481
00:38:57,607 --> 00:38:59,733
It's been one accident after another.

482
00:38:59,734 --> 00:39:01,652
Goodness gracious me.

483
00:39:19,504 --> 00:39:20,587
Wait.

484
00:39:20,588 --> 00:39:22,214
It's fine, I'll get it.

485
00:39:22,215 --> 00:39:24,549
Using shoes as an excuse…

486
00:39:30,306 --> 00:39:32,683
You've reached the Public Health Center.

487
00:39:32,684 --> 00:39:34,476
Ms. Hwang.

488
00:39:34,477 --> 00:39:35,811
Yes, Ms. Hari.

489
00:39:35,812 --> 00:39:38,313
Would it be okay
if I went home from here today?

490
00:39:38,314 --> 00:39:39,731
Is something going on?

491
00:39:39,732 --> 00:39:41,775
I just need to look into something.

492
00:39:41,776 --> 00:39:44,945
I see. Are you also going to Jangmokdo?

493
00:39:44,946 --> 00:39:45,947
Huh?

494
00:39:46,614 --> 00:39:48,365
How did you know that?

495
00:39:48,366 --> 00:39:52,411
Well, Dr. Hyeon also said
he was going there to look into something.

496
00:39:52,412 --> 00:39:54,539
- I guess you can tag along.
- Ah.

497
00:39:55,540 --> 00:39:57,417
Okay, be safe.

498
00:39:58,084 --> 00:39:59,167
Okay, Ms. Hwang.

499
00:39:59,168 --> 00:40:00,670
Mmm. Right then.

500
00:40:03,589 --> 00:40:07,009
Gosh, these are so dry.
Got to eat them faster.

501
00:40:07,010 --> 00:40:09,095
SCHEDULE FOR THE SECOND
HALF-YEAR TRAINING SESSION

502
00:40:09,679 --> 00:40:13,348
Dr. Yong, looks like you'll
have to attend this over the weekend.

503
00:40:13,349 --> 00:40:16,476
You'll be transferred to
a different post soon after that,

504
00:40:16,477 --> 00:40:19,647
so I guess this'll be
your last training session already.

505
00:40:20,690 --> 00:40:22,316
Time sure flies.

506
00:40:23,276 --> 00:40:24,860
This is a good thing, I guess.

507
00:40:24,861 --> 00:40:26,904
You always felt so cooped up here.

508
00:40:31,075 --> 00:40:33,703
Ms. Eom, do you want to
attend it together?

509
00:40:34,662 --> 00:40:36,288
It's during the weekend anyway,

510
00:40:36,289 --> 00:40:39,374
so a date on the mainland
might be a nice change of pace.

511
00:40:39,375 --> 00:40:43,962
There's also this really fancy restaurant
I want to take you to.

512
00:40:43,963 --> 00:40:46,256
Let's carve up some steaks and whatnot.

513
00:40:46,257 --> 00:40:47,258
What do you say?

514
00:40:50,178 --> 00:40:54,265
I guess I shouldn't look like a slob
since we're going to a fancy restaurant.

515
00:40:55,391 --> 00:40:59,020
Since we're going out for steak,
I guess I might as well splurge a little.

516
00:41:11,407 --> 00:41:13,700
How much… This is insane.

517
00:41:13,701 --> 00:41:17,204
How can they charge so much
for a piece of cloth?

518
00:41:17,205 --> 00:41:19,581
People must be swimming
in money or something.

519
00:41:19,582 --> 00:41:21,458
Are they out of their…

520
00:41:21,459 --> 00:41:23,919
What is it even made of?

521
00:41:23,920 --> 00:41:24,921
Damn it.

522
00:41:30,885 --> 00:41:34,639
DON'T SKIP YOUR MEALS, DR. DO

523
00:42:04,460 --> 00:42:06,628
Jiui, can you spare me a moment?

524
00:42:06,629 --> 00:42:08,506
I'll be waiting outside
until you come out.
:cue

525
00:42:26,774 --> 00:42:31,528
JANGMOKDO DOCK

526
00:42:31,529 --> 00:42:36,033
JANGMOKDO, PYEONDONGDO

527
00:42:37,493 --> 00:42:38,702
- Hello.
-  Oh my, hello.

528
00:42:38,703 --> 00:42:40,662
- You're from the Pyeondong Health Center?
- Yes.

529
00:42:40,663 --> 00:42:42,497
I've been waiting for you.

530
00:42:42,498 --> 00:42:45,000
I'm Lee Seongu from
the Jangmok Health Center.

531
00:42:45,001 --> 00:42:46,960
- Hello.
- Thank you for your cooperation.

532
00:42:46,961 --> 00:42:49,129
Not at all. The helipad's this way.

533
00:42:49,130 --> 00:42:50,548
- Right this way.
- Right.

534
00:42:52,049 --> 00:42:53,550
Mind your step.

535
00:42:53,551 --> 00:42:55,678
I heard the chopper couldn't land.

536
00:42:56,554 --> 00:42:57,637
Right.

537
00:42:57,638 --> 00:43:01,641
They rushed the construction so much
that they didn't have a lighting setup,

538
00:43:01,642 --> 00:43:04,853
and the helipad was so disorganized
that the chopper couldn't land.

539
00:43:04,854 --> 00:43:07,856
Was the Pyeondongdo incident
also caused by lighting issues?

540
00:43:07,857 --> 00:43:09,691
We're not sure yet.

541
00:43:09,692 --> 00:43:11,735
They're still investigating.

542
00:43:11,736 --> 00:43:12,819
We all know why.

543
00:43:12,820 --> 00:43:15,030
My buddy's stationed at Gayeongdo,

544
00:43:15,031 --> 00:43:17,699
and things are a mess
due to lighting issues there too.

545
00:43:17,700 --> 00:43:22,746
I heard those bastards told them
to only transfer the patients by boat.

546
00:43:22,747 --> 00:43:25,875
What the hell can we do on an island
when they block off the air routes?

547
00:43:26,918 --> 00:43:28,085
Lighting…

548
00:43:33,674 --> 00:43:37,385
Would you mind giving us
that doctor's contact information?

549
00:43:37,386 --> 00:43:38,637
Sorry?

550
00:43:38,638 --> 00:43:40,139
On the day of the accident…

551
00:43:42,099 --> 00:43:45,228
I don't think I saw any lights
at the helipad either.

552
00:43:48,814 --> 00:43:49,898
Yes, hello.

553
00:43:49,899 --> 00:43:52,442
I'm Yuk Hari,
a nurse at the Pyeondong Health Center.

554
00:43:52,443 --> 00:43:55,362
I'm looking into lighting issues
at helipads in Yeopoong-gun.

555
00:43:55,363 --> 00:43:58,031
Hello. I'm Hyeon Chiyeon,
a PH doc at Pyeondong.

556
00:43:58,032 --> 00:44:00,408
I heard they built
a new helipad there recently.

557
00:44:00,409 --> 00:44:03,036
I heard the last time
you had an emergency patient,

558
00:44:03,037 --> 00:44:05,497
you transferred them by boat
rather than a chopper.

559
00:44:05,498 --> 00:44:07,415
Is everything working properly?

560
00:44:07,416 --> 00:44:08,960
Was there a reason you did that?

561
00:44:09,919 --> 00:44:12,213
Oh, yes. Uh-huh.

562
00:44:13,923 --> 00:44:16,216
- Lighting issues at the helipads?
-  I understand.

563
00:44:16,217 --> 00:44:17,300
Thank you.

564
00:44:17,301 --> 00:44:20,553
So the Yujae Health Center
has stopped using medical helicopters?

565
00:44:20,554 --> 00:44:24,099
If the lighting isn't finished yet,
that would impede landings and takeoffs.

566
00:44:24,100 --> 00:44:26,309
- Have they wrapped up construction there?
- I see.

567
00:44:26,310 --> 00:44:27,560
They suspended it?

568
00:44:27,561 --> 00:44:29,772
So you're not using the helipad at all?

569
00:44:30,690 --> 00:44:32,984
Uh. I understand. Okay.

570
00:44:57,341 --> 00:44:58,342
Oh, my.

571
00:45:01,929 --> 00:45:07,059
You two catch up.
I'm going to go to the supermarket.

572
00:45:16,444 --> 00:45:17,695
Thanks for coming.

573
00:45:19,572 --> 00:45:21,741
I knew you'd keep waiting
until I came out.

574
00:45:23,409 --> 00:45:24,952
But I'm not here to hear you out.

575
00:45:27,330 --> 00:45:28,956
I'm here to tell you about me.

576
00:45:33,753 --> 00:45:37,340
I tried so hard to get past what you said
about how we didn't deserve to be happy.

577
00:45:39,008 --> 00:45:40,509
Though it felt unfair to Seonu.

578
00:45:42,762 --> 00:45:43,763
But…

579
00:45:45,765 --> 00:45:47,475
I just couldn't do it.

580
00:45:49,810 --> 00:45:51,354
I think you were right.

581
00:45:52,521 --> 00:45:53,898
We don't deserve to be happy.

582
00:45:56,609 --> 00:45:59,153
So I don't need your consolation now,
after all this time.

583
00:46:05,868 --> 00:46:07,745
I won't leave you by yourself this time.

584
00:46:12,291 --> 00:46:13,584
I looked into it.

585
00:46:14,377 --> 00:46:16,836
PH docs can also get transferred
to a different station

586
00:46:16,837 --> 00:46:18,380
if they have a valid reason.

587
00:46:18,381 --> 00:46:22,718
If we were to get Gangseok to explain
your condition to the county office,

588
00:46:23,636 --> 00:46:24,762
you can get transferred.

589
00:46:28,766 --> 00:46:31,519
Come with me, Jiui.

590
00:46:36,982 --> 00:46:38,192
Will leaving this place…

591
00:46:43,364 --> 00:46:44,907
help me forget Seonu?
:cue

592
00:47:08,264 --> 00:47:10,933
Why didn't we think of that
in the first place?

593
00:47:11,434 --> 00:47:14,937
It was pitch black out there
because they hadn't set up the lighting,

594
00:47:15,771 --> 00:47:17,814
and they let Dr. Do take the fall for it

595
00:47:17,815 --> 00:47:19,859
to hide their shoddy construction work.

596
00:47:20,609 --> 00:47:23,904
I'm going to bring this up
and make them take full responsibility.

597
00:47:25,781 --> 00:47:28,242
- Don't do it.
- What?

598
00:47:30,453 --> 00:47:33,371
I'll do it.

599
00:47:33,372 --> 00:47:35,457
I'm a PH doc who's only here for a year.

600
00:47:35,458 --> 00:47:38,294
But no good will come of you
making an enemy of Yeopoong-gun.

601
00:47:40,671 --> 00:47:45,551
The chief told me that you might be
staying on this island for a long time.

602
00:47:47,803 --> 00:47:48,887
Oh.

603
00:47:51,932 --> 00:47:53,142
Please let me do it.

604
00:47:54,643 --> 00:47:57,313
Since it's a PH doc matter,
let a PH doc handle it.

605
00:48:17,249 --> 00:48:19,585
What are you waiting for?
Hurry up and go tell him.

606
00:48:42,483 --> 00:48:43,942
Dr. Do!

607
00:48:47,238 --> 00:48:48,239
Ms. Yuk.

608
00:48:49,240 --> 00:48:50,324
The helicopter crash…

609
00:48:51,408 --> 00:48:54,703
It was caused by Yeopoong-gun's
reckless helipad construction projects.

610
00:48:55,704 --> 00:48:57,830
I looked into it all day today,

611
00:48:57,831 --> 00:49:01,417
and apparently,
out of the 20 new helipads they built,

612
00:49:01,418 --> 00:49:03,128
only three had functioning lights.

613
00:49:03,837 --> 00:49:05,630
The lighting issue was also the reason

614
00:49:05,631 --> 00:49:07,882
none of the CCTVs caught what happened.

615
00:49:07,883 --> 00:49:09,842
So what I mean to say is…

616
00:49:16,058 --> 00:49:18,811
The accident wasn't your fault, Dr. Do.

617
00:49:22,773 --> 00:49:24,817
You need to know that.

618
00:49:26,569 --> 00:49:28,404
That it wasn't your fault.

619
00:49:33,117 --> 00:49:35,661
It wasn't your fault, Dr. Do.

620
00:49:41,166 --> 00:49:42,835
Is that why you…

621
00:49:44,753 --> 00:49:47,256
kept visiting all those islands?
You did it for me?

622
00:49:51,468 --> 00:49:53,345
So please stop hiding.

623
00:49:56,307 --> 00:50:00,436
I can't be by your side
if you keep hiding like that.

624
00:50:29,256 --> 00:50:30,799
I'll stop hiding now.
:cue

625
00:51:26,647 --> 00:51:28,981
Ta-da.

626
00:51:55,718 --> 00:51:57,093
Ms. Eom.

627
00:51:57,094 --> 00:51:58,095
Is it too much?

628
00:51:59,680 --> 00:52:01,097
Yes, it is too much.

629
00:52:03,016 --> 00:52:05,226
It's too much because you look so pretty!

630
00:52:05,227 --> 00:52:06,894
Ah!

631
00:52:06,895 --> 00:52:09,481
Here are some flowers I brought for you.

632
00:52:13,861 --> 00:52:15,446
Thank you.

633
00:52:16,530 --> 00:52:18,990
I don't know if I put on weight
or something,

634
00:52:18,991 --> 00:52:20,950
but doesn't it look a bit tight on me?

635
00:52:20,951 --> 00:52:23,369
Tight? Not at all.

636
00:52:23,370 --> 00:52:25,705
You look so pretty.
You look like an angel.

637
00:52:25,706 --> 00:52:27,249
Come on.

638
00:52:29,877 --> 00:52:32,044
Our ferry will be leaving soon. Let's go.

639
00:52:32,045 --> 00:52:33,297
- Come on.
- Let's go.

640
00:52:42,931 --> 00:52:44,348
Dr. Do!

641
00:52:44,349 --> 00:52:47,852
Hey, what are you doing here on a weekend?

642
00:52:47,853 --> 00:52:50,939
I brought this so we can have it together.

643
00:53:03,619 --> 00:53:07,246
I was really craving pasta
when I woke up this morning,

644
00:53:07,247 --> 00:53:11,959
but I made too much
since I'm used to making two servings.

645
00:53:11,960 --> 00:53:13,796
Dig in.

646
00:53:15,172 --> 00:53:17,049
This used to be my grandma's favorite.

647
00:53:17,716 --> 00:53:18,717
Thanks for this.

648
00:53:26,475 --> 00:53:28,101
- Delicious, isn't it?
- Mm-hmm.

649
00:53:30,729 --> 00:53:34,023
That's right, Dr. Chiyeon said
he filed a request at the county office

650
00:53:34,024 --> 00:53:37,360
and demanded corrections from the outlets
that published those articles.

651
00:53:37,361 --> 00:53:40,113
- Ah.
- They'll publish correction articles soon.

652
00:53:42,658 --> 00:53:43,951
This isn't over yet.

653
00:53:44,576 --> 00:53:46,577
I'll keep an eye on them
till the very end.

654
00:53:46,578 --> 00:53:49,623
We have to make sure everyone
gives a proper apology.

655
00:53:53,085 --> 00:53:54,585
This is good enough for me.

656
00:53:56,880 --> 00:53:58,549
Eat up. The noodles will get mushy.
:cue

657
00:54:06,515 --> 00:54:07,558
Excuse me.

658
00:54:23,824 --> 00:54:27,202
How can they charge so much for one meal?

659
00:54:29,329 --> 00:54:31,998
Would you mind if I ordered for us?

660
00:54:31,999 --> 00:54:34,835
I've actually read up
on their best dishes in advance.

661
00:54:35,627 --> 00:54:36,670
Sure.

662
00:54:37,713 --> 00:54:39,630
We'd like the A course

663
00:54:39,631 --> 00:54:43,384
with a medium tenderloin
and some caviar on the side, please.

664
00:54:43,385 --> 00:54:44,468
Okay.

665
00:54:44,469 --> 00:54:45,512
Would you like some wine?

666
00:54:47,598 --> 00:54:49,141
How much is…

667
00:54:50,058 --> 00:54:51,976
Do you have Château de Lune d'Or?

668
00:54:51,977 --> 00:54:53,227
Yes, we do.

669
00:54:53,228 --> 00:54:57,690
We'd like that,
and the jamón charcuterie board as well.

670
00:54:57,691 --> 00:54:58,983
What grade is the jamón?

671
00:54:58,984 --> 00:55:00,736
It's 100% Ibérico de Bellota.

672
00:55:01,737 --> 00:55:03,571
Sounds great. That'll be all.

673
00:55:03,572 --> 00:55:05,240
Yes, sir. Right away.

674
00:55:10,078 --> 00:55:12,456
You're so pretty today.

675
00:55:15,250 --> 00:55:17,919
I get it, so please stop saying that.

676
00:55:18,503 --> 00:55:21,381
But you really do look super pretty today.

677
00:55:28,305 --> 00:55:29,306
Thank you.

678
00:55:34,436 --> 00:55:35,437
Enjoy your meal.

679
00:55:38,398 --> 00:55:41,860
At these prices,
you'd expect a bigger portion.

680
00:55:46,490 --> 00:55:47,532
Try this.

681
00:55:48,784 --> 00:55:50,661
Didn't we order the same dish?

682
00:55:51,787 --> 00:55:52,788
You're right.

683
00:55:53,497 --> 00:55:56,249
But it tastes better
when we feed it to each other like this.

684
00:55:57,209 --> 00:55:58,626
You're so cheesy.

685
00:55:58,627 --> 00:56:01,128
Being cheesy's what dating's all about.

686
00:56:01,129 --> 00:56:02,213
Here, say "ah."

687
00:56:02,214 --> 00:56:03,548
Ah.

688
00:56:07,969 --> 00:56:09,053
How do you like it?

689
00:56:09,054 --> 00:56:10,097
Delicious, isn't it?

690
00:56:19,022 --> 00:56:21,566
- You can order more if you'd like.
- Mmm.

691
00:56:27,656 --> 00:56:29,241
Seriously?

692
00:56:30,450 --> 00:56:31,618
What's wrong?

693
00:56:32,661 --> 00:56:36,622
The others got to enjoy getting stranded
due to terrible weather.

694
00:56:36,623 --> 00:56:40,084
It's so unfair that we should get
such clear skies during our visit.

695
00:56:40,085 --> 00:56:41,712
Of all the things to complain about.

696
00:56:42,921 --> 00:56:45,965
Dr. Yong, would you mind
waiting here for a short while?

697
00:56:45,966 --> 00:56:47,049
What for?

698
00:56:47,050 --> 00:56:51,388
Maybe it's because of the tight clothes,
but I've been feeling stuffy all day.

699
00:56:52,472 --> 00:56:55,307
So I'm just going to grab
some antacids at a pharmacy.

700
00:56:55,308 --> 00:56:57,518
Mmm. Let me bring you one.

701
00:56:57,519 --> 00:56:59,311
I'm not a baby, okay?

702
00:56:59,312 --> 00:57:01,606
Hold this for me. I'll be right back.

703
00:57:04,234 --> 00:57:05,944
- Don't take too long.
- Okay.

704
00:57:12,743 --> 00:57:14,869
I'd like some antacids, please.

705
00:57:14,870 --> 00:57:15,871
Okay.

706
00:57:23,378 --> 00:57:24,921
- That'll be 4,100 won.
- Okay.

707
00:57:30,177 --> 00:57:31,178
Here you go.

708
00:57:42,230 --> 00:57:44,899
The ship bound for
Pyeondongdo, Pyeondongdo is now departing.

709
00:57:44,900 --> 00:57:46,610
What's taking her so long?

710
00:57:47,194 --> 00:57:49,529
We'll miss the last ferry at this rate.

711
00:57:51,031 --> 00:57:52,782
I guess that might be even better.

712
00:57:55,911 --> 00:57:58,287
Uh.

713
00:58:31,279 --> 00:58:32,947
I'm late.

714
00:58:32,948 --> 00:58:34,616
Oh, man…

715
00:58:36,743 --> 00:58:37,952
Dr. Yong!

716
00:58:37,953 --> 00:58:39,161
Ms. Eom!

717
00:58:39,162 --> 00:58:40,955
Why weren't you picking up?

718
00:58:40,956 --> 00:58:42,832
I'm sorry. I had to go to the bathroom.

719
00:58:42,833 --> 00:58:44,084
Okay. Let's hurry.
:cue

720
00:59:10,735 --> 00:59:12,445
Are you all right?

721
00:59:15,490 --> 00:59:16,616
I'm sorry.

722
00:59:17,284 --> 00:59:20,578
I'm sure my sudden leave must have
put a lot of strain on everyone.

723
00:59:20,579 --> 00:59:23,455
Come on, things like this
happen out of the blue all the time.

724
00:59:23,456 --> 00:59:25,000
Don't let it get to you.

725
00:59:32,757 --> 00:59:36,553
By the way, shouldn't those articles
have come out by now?

726
00:59:37,929 --> 00:59:40,931
You're sure you told the county office,

727
00:59:40,932 --> 00:59:43,935
the Ministry of Health and Welfare,
and the reporters, right?

728
00:59:46,855 --> 00:59:47,898
Yes.

729
00:59:48,565 --> 00:59:51,234
Then why haven't we heard
a peep from them?

730
00:59:51,860 --> 00:59:56,155
I mean, they were all up in arms when
they were trying to ruin someone's life,

731
00:59:56,156 --> 00:59:58,699
but they sure don't seem
very interested in the truth.

732
00:59:58,700 --> 01:00:00,327
So frustrating.

733
01:00:04,706 --> 01:00:06,750
When are they going to come out anyway?

734
01:00:07,542 --> 01:00:11,003
PYEONDONGDO HELICOPTER PH DOC

735
01:00:12,380 --> 01:00:14,591
- It's out!
-  Where?

736
01:00:18,303 --> 01:00:22,222
"Health Center PH doc at Pyeondong
where helicopter crash occurred

737
01:00:22,223 --> 01:00:25,142
revealed to have been
taking psychiatric medication"?

738
01:00:32,692 --> 01:00:34,193
"It has recently come to light

739
01:00:34,194 --> 01:00:36,737
that the PH doc stationed
at Pyeondong Health Center,

740
01:00:36,738 --> 01:00:38,989
the recent site
of a fatal helicopter crash,

741
01:00:38,990 --> 01:00:42,159
had a history of receiving
psychiatric treatment and medication."

742
01:00:42,160 --> 01:00:44,495
"This has raised concerns
that the misdiagnosis

743
01:00:44,496 --> 01:00:48,248
may have been caused
by a lapse in judgment

744
01:00:48,249 --> 01:00:50,251
due to the medication he is taking."

745
01:00:51,670 --> 01:00:54,338
"In response, Choi Hyangmi,
the director of public health,

746
01:00:54,339 --> 01:00:58,342
has stated that she will be putting
the PH doc taking psychiatric medication

747
01:00:58,343 --> 01:01:01,262
on standby and consider removing him
from his post."

748
01:01:02,138 --> 01:01:03,222
What the hell?

749
01:01:03,223 --> 01:01:07,769
So they've resorted to spreading fake news
just to shirk the blame now?

750
01:01:08,478 --> 01:01:10,270
What the heck are they talking about?

751
01:01:10,271 --> 01:01:12,273
What's this about a PH doc on medication?

752
01:01:18,196 --> 01:01:19,531
It's all true.

753
01:01:26,162 --> 01:01:27,372
Let me look into this.

754
01:01:27,998 --> 01:01:29,332
No, Dr. Hyeon.

755
01:01:29,916 --> 01:01:31,710
- But still, we should at least--
- Just don't!

756
01:01:32,919 --> 01:01:34,004
I'm okay.

757
01:01:53,440 --> 01:01:54,690
Oh, gosh…

758
01:01:54,691 --> 01:01:56,108
How could something like this…

759
01:02:06,036 --> 01:02:09,329
Those meds can cause
side effects like memory loss, dizziness,

760
01:02:09,330 --> 01:02:10,748
and hallucinations…

761
01:02:10,749 --> 01:02:14,084
It is a horrific incident caused
by a public health doctor's misdiagnosis.
:cue

762
01:02:14,085 --> 01:02:16,837
Appendicitis is often tricky to diagnose.

763
01:02:16,838 --> 01:02:19,089
If we explain your condition
to the county office…

764
01:02:19,090 --> 01:02:20,799
How dare you come here!

765
01:02:20,800 --> 01:02:21,843
How dare you!

766
01:02:27,348 --> 01:02:28,475
Dr. Do.

767
01:02:40,195 --> 01:02:41,404
Dr. Do, are you okay?

768
01:02:45,742 --> 01:02:47,701
Don't worry about a thing.

769
01:02:47,702 --> 01:02:49,996
I'm going to prove that those meds

770
01:02:51,164 --> 01:02:55,376
had nothing to do with
your diagnosis, okay?

771
01:02:59,756 --> 01:03:04,427
I can't take this anymore.

772
01:03:09,974 --> 01:03:11,976
I'm so scared of being on an island.

773
01:04:26,926 --> 01:04:29,636
I CAN'T BE BY YOUR SIDE

774
01:04:29,637 --> 01:04:36,186
IF YOU KEEP HIDING LIKE THAT

775
01:04:49,532 --> 01:04:52,911
PICK THE CUTIE PIE HERE

776
01:04:53,494 --> 01:04:56,997
CUTIE PIE? WERE YOU LOOKING FOR ME?

777
01:04:56,998 --> 01:05:00,919
IN ONE TAKE WITH NO BLOOPERS?

778
01:05:05,006 --> 01:05:07,926
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

779
01:05:08,676 --> 01:05:11,553
Do you really think leaving the island
will help him recover?

780
01:05:11,554 --> 01:05:14,598
Jiui. You might actually
have to step down as a doctor for good.

781
01:05:14,599 --> 01:05:16,391
It just sounds a bit selfish.

782
01:05:16,392 --> 01:05:19,436
The only way to treat unbearable pain
is to run away from it.

783
01:05:19,437 --> 01:05:21,271
You must have struggled so much here,

784
01:05:21,272 --> 01:05:23,065
surrounded on all sides by the ocean.

785
01:05:23,066 --> 01:05:26,485
Surrounded or not, I wanted to
hang in there because I had you, Ms. Yuk.

786
01:05:26,486 --> 01:05:29,446
Looks like we just keep having to
apologize to each other.

787
01:05:29,447 --> 01:05:31,532
That's why Jiui wants to leave.

788
01:05:32,533 --> 01:05:33,952
It's because he wants to live.

789
01:05:37,956 --> 01:05:39,958
Translated by Yoon Hyuk Park

